parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause loss of control, accidents, or leave the driver stranded, especially at high speeds.
symptoms: makes noise in the first gear at initial start from a dead stop.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the four-wheel drive selector button can cause the vehicle to not engage into four-wheel drive, leading to loss of traction and control, especially in off-road or slippery conditions.
symptoms: failure to engage into four-wheel drive

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the EBCM can cause the Anti-lock Braking System (ABS) to malfunction, leading to reduced vehicle safety and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: the ABS motor continues to run
the ABS system fails to function properly
the vehicle experiences reduced braking performance.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the upper and/or lower ball joints can cause the front tires to collapse, leading to loss of control and potentially resulting in major accidents.
symptoms: Unusual noises or vibrations from the front suspension
front tires may collapse or sag.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the metal that holds the recliner lever on the seats can cause the lever to break, resulting in discomfort and inconvenience for the occupants.
symptoms: The recliner lever breaks or becomes loose

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The corrosion of aluminum wheel rims can cause the tire seal to break, leading to air leaks and potentially causing a loss of control or accidents, especially at high speeds.
symptoms: Heavy flaking of the wheel rim
frequent need to scrape and reseal the wheel rims.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden loss of tire tread can cause a loss of control, accidents, or injuries, especially at high speeds.
